> **Agent-facing tool rule:** The PM normally does not edit this file.

Before product work:

- Read @AGENTS.md and @INDEX.md.
- Run the lightweight structural reconciliation in @AGENTS.md; preserve and integrate manually
  added product folders/files automatically.
- Follow @agents/pm-chief.md as the default Chief PM coordinator.
- Ground relevant work in @product-docs/product-vision.md.
- Apply @_workspace_setup_docs/skills/apply-pmos-struct.md after meaningful workspace changes.

Keep the workspace focused:

- Fit structure and routes to product stage, PM scope, and active work.
- Do not recreate research, design, data, roadmap, launch, or communication lanes unless the current
  context earns them.
- Put reusable workflow and output rules under `product-practices/skills/`, exact formats under
  `product-practices/templates/`, and examples or standing guidance under
  `product-practices/references/`.
- Synchronize product folders, skills, templates, references, specialists, Chief PM routes, and
  indexes whenever one layer changes.

Preserve memory:

- Keep nearest and root indexes current.
- Preserve raw input under an artifact-local `raw/` archive and create summaries or synthesized
  artifacts separately.
- Save recommendations, prioritization, MVP scope, and next steps in `product-docs/outcomes/`.
- Keep PM OS machinery out of the user's product artifacts.
